quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  9,38,"You who believe, what is wrong with you when you are told: ´March off in God´s cause!\"? Do you feel weighted down to the ground? Are you more satisfied with worldly life than with the [prospect of the] Hereafter? The comfort of worldly life will mean so little in the Hereafter"
  9,39,"Unless you march away, He will punish you with painful torment and substitute you with some other folk. You will not harm Him in any way, for God is Capable of everything"
  9,40,"If you do not support him, well God did support him when those who disbelieved expelled him as the second of two, when they were both in the Cave, as he told his companion: \"Do not worry; for God is with us.\" So God sent His serenity down on him and aided him with troops you did not see, and placed the word of those who disbelieved lowest, while God´s word remained supreme. God is Powerful, Wise"
  9,41,"March forth light or heavy [-armed], and strive in God´s cause with your property and persons. That will be best for you if you only realize it"
  9,42,"If there had been some goods to be acquired closer by and on a shorter journey, they would have followed you; but the expedition seemed much too far for them. They will swear by God; \"If we could have managed to, we would have left along with you (all).\" They destroy their own souls while God knows what liars they are"